WEBVTT

1
00:00:06.006 --> 00:00:09.009
{\an8}(epic theme playing)

2
00:00:11.000 --> 00:00:17.074
Do you want subtitles for any video?
-=[ ai.OpenSubtitles.com ]=-

3
00:00:54.179 --> 00:00:56.222
{\an8}♪

4
00:01:49.901 --> 00:01:51.903
(theme concludes)

5
00:01:53.905 --> 00:01:56.908
(tense music playing)

6
00:02:01.913 --> 00:02:03.915
(indistinct chatter)

7
00:02:05.083 --> 00:02:08.023
Tyroshi captain:
These are our terms.

8
00:02:08.024 --> 00:02:10.963
One hundred of your
golden dragons.

9
00:02:10.964 --> 00:02:13.758
- Tyland Lannister: Per ship?
- (captain chuckles)

10
00:02:13.759 --> 00:02:15.092
captain:
Per man.

11
00:02:15.093 --> 00:02:17.095
Tyland: I could not produce
such a coin.

12
00:02:17.096 --> 00:02:18.303
even if
I wanted to.

13
00:02:18.304 --> 00:02:20.097
Myrish captain:
Again. you plead poverty.

14
00:02:20.098 --> 00:02:22.976
It is hollow stuff
from the mouth of a Lannister.

15
00:02:22.977 --> 00:02:24.790
Whose very stables
and sculleries

16
00:02:24.791 --> 00:02:26.603
are carved into
a mountain of gold.

17
00:02:26.604 --> 00:02:29.440
And we will need it
before this war is done.

18
00:02:29.441 --> 00:02:32.277
Break the blockade
and it will benefit you.

19
00:02:32.278 --> 00:02:34.529
Do you think that we lack
for buyers

20
00:02:34.530 --> 00:02:36.781
for our tapestries
and perfumes?

21
00:02:36.782 --> 00:02:39.075
We sell where
we please.

22
00:02:39.076 --> 00:02:40.993
blockade or no.

23
00:02:40.994 --> 00:02:43.829
Essos is as rich
as it is vast.

24
00:02:43.830 --> 00:02:48.126
It seems you need us
more than we need you.

25
00:02:48.127 --> 00:02:50.962
- (sighs)
- (indistinct chatter)

26
00:02:51.963 --> 00:02:53.214
The Stepstones.

27
00:02:55.717 --> 00:02:57.676
(scoffs)
What of them?

28
00:02:57.677 --> 00:02:59.637
Give us the Stepstones.

29
00:03:00.805 --> 00:03:02.474
A smattering
of rocks...

30
00:03:03.308 --> 00:03:06.685
hardly a sacrifice
to the lords of Westeros.

31
00:03:06.686 --> 00:03:11.816
I... Those rocks have been
disputed for a generation.

32
00:03:13.151 --> 00:03:14.319
Your...

33
00:03:15.236 --> 00:03:19.324
pirates have waylaid ships.
taken slaves. cargo...

34
00:03:19.325 --> 00:03:22.035
Give them to us outright.
if you prevail.

35
00:03:22.036 --> 00:03:24.162
and all that
will cease.

36
00:03:24.163 --> 00:03:26.080
We will impose
a simple tax

37
00:03:26.081 --> 00:03:27.998
on those
passing through.

38
00:03:27.999 --> 00:03:30.334
Recoup the losses
we took fighting

39
00:03:30.335 --> 00:03:32.169
- the Velaryon hordes.
- Tyland: Extortion.

40
00:03:32.170 --> 00:03:34.005
You will drive up
the price of basic goods.

41
00:03:34.006 --> 00:03:37.342
It is better than
starving. surely.

42
00:03:41.012 --> 00:03:44.015
Myrish captain: A fleet of warships. then.
sailing at your command.

43
00:03:44.016 --> 00:03:46.184
- They would break the blockade...
- Tyland: Hm.

44
00:03:46.185 --> 00:03:47.852
...and hold
the passage.

45
00:03:53.608 --> 00:03:54.859
Very well.

46
00:03:58.697 --> 00:04:01.491
The prince regent may
have me hanged for this.

47
00:04:01.492 --> 00:04:03.680
With the armada
we send now.

48
00:04:03.681 --> 00:04:05.859
you can topple
the prince regent

49
00:04:05.860 --> 00:04:08.039
and sit
the Iron Throne yourself.

50
00:04:12.377 --> 00:04:16.840
- (grunts)
- Myrish captain: Of course. there is one more condition.

51
00:04:16.841 --> 00:04:18.049
(sighs)

52
00:04:19.384 --> 00:04:20.718
Tyland:
I was...

53
00:04:20.719 --> 00:04:22.720
rather set on a bath
and a flagon of wine.

54
00:04:22.721 --> 00:04:24.723
Myrish captain:
The commander of our fleet

55
00:04:24.724 --> 00:04:26.223
must agree
to go with you.

56
00:04:26.224 --> 00:04:29.185
His name is Lohar.
The sailors are fiercely loyal to him.

57
00:04:29.186 --> 00:04:30.687
If. if he does
not lead them.

58
00:04:30.688 --> 00:04:32.313
they will not fight.

59
00:04:34.816 --> 00:04:36.067
Very well.

60
00:04:36.735 --> 00:04:39.362
Let us meet this
commander then.

61
00:04:40.405 --> 00:04:42.740
(clears throat. grunts)

62
00:04:42.741 --> 00:04:45.785
- (flies buzzing)
- (indistinct chatter)

63
00:04:50.498 --> 00:04:51.750
Admiral Lohar...

64
00:04:52.917 --> 00:04:55.128
this is
Tyland Lannister.

65
00:04:55.129 --> 00:04:57.005
of Casterly Rock.

66
00:04:57.964 --> 00:05:00.425
Well met.
Lord Tywin.

67
00:05:01.176 --> 00:05:02.427
Uh...

68
00:05:04.763 --> 00:05:06.765
it's Tyland.

69
00:05:08.600 --> 00:05:10.268
What sort of
man are you?

70
00:05:11.686 --> 00:05:14.939
- I beg your pardon?
- A poet...

71
00:05:15.940 --> 00:05:17.150
a philosopher?

72
00:05:17.692 --> 00:05:20.445
I am the master of ships
at King's Landing.

73
00:05:20.945 --> 00:05:24.157
- You're thin.
- But also tall.

74
00:05:26.785 --> 00:05:30.246
I will not sail with a man
who cannot best me.

75
00:05:30.247 --> 00:05:32.436
(quiet laughter)

76
00:05:32.437 --> 00:05:34.626
(indistinct chatter)

77
00:05:35.960 --> 00:05:37.504
At. at what?

78
00:05:40.548 --> 00:05:43.592
(tense music playing)

79
00:05:43.593 --> 00:05:46.638
{\an8}(grumbles. roars)

80
00:05:58.525 --> 00:06:01.528
♪

81
00:06:07.867 --> 00:06:10.495
(people wailing. screaming)

82
00:06:20.171 --> 00:06:22.382
(music fades out)

83
00:06:23.383 --> 00:06:25.385
(Orwyle pouring tea)

84
00:06:26.928 --> 00:06:29.014
Some rum wouldn't go amiss.

85
00:06:30.223 --> 00:06:31.683
Your Grace.

86
00:06:32.434 --> 00:06:34.060
Just a little.

87
00:06:34.853 --> 00:06:37.063
(distant bell tolling)

88
00:06:42.694 --> 00:06:44.863
You're a good man.
Orwyle.

89
00:06:49.075 --> 00:06:50.805
(door opens)

90
00:06:50.806 --> 00:06:52.537
(Aegon drinking)

91
00:06:55.540 --> 00:06:57.145
(birds chirping)

92
00:06:57.146 --> 00:06:58.752
A word. Your Grace?

93
00:07:00.045 --> 00:07:03.048
(exhales. clears throat)

94
00:07:17.062 --> 00:07:19.063
(door closes)

95
00:07:19.064 --> 00:07:21.941
I must ask you.
Your Grace. to steel yourself.

96
00:07:23.068 --> 00:07:25.319
We must leave
King's Landing. quickly.

97
00:07:25.320 --> 00:07:27.572
and we will not return
for some time.

98
00:07:29.449 --> 00:07:33.953
- What?
- The Pretender has found three new riders for her dragons.

99
00:07:33.954 --> 00:07:37.290
- That's impossible.
- Your brother thought the same.

100
00:07:37.291 --> 00:07:40.210
He flew to challenge her
and was rebuffed.

101
00:07:40.211 --> 00:07:42.253
Fled in terror.
from what I hear.

102
00:07:44.464 --> 00:07:46.383
He deserves no less.

103
00:07:46.591 --> 00:07:50.595
Be that as it may.
he has gone in fury to Sharp Point...

104
00:07:51.262 --> 00:07:53.932
and laid waste
to the whole of the town.

105
00:07:55.308 --> 00:07:57.769
Fucking mad cunt.

106
00:08:00.313 --> 00:08:01.773
She really
did it then?

107
00:08:02.524 --> 00:08:04.109
I fear so.

108
00:08:05.777 --> 00:08:08.655
So. what was
the fucking point in all this then?

109
00:08:09.989 --> 00:08:12.887
The gods are cruel.
Your Grace.

110
00:08:12.888 --> 00:08:16.902
but I hope
you can see the urgency.

111
00:08:16.903 --> 00:08:20.917
No. no. I am the king.
Why must I run?

112
00:08:21.334 --> 00:08:23.795
Because the prince regent
is going to kill you.

113
00:08:28.133 --> 00:08:29.299
You were
in danger before.

114
00:08:29.300 --> 00:08:31.739
and now. he is thwarted
and he is angry.

115
00:08:31.740 --> 00:08:34.180
There is no telling
what he will do.

116
00:08:34.181 --> 00:08:35.848
but we have
an opportunity

117
00:08:35.849 --> 00:08:38.893
- while he is away...
- An opportunity to push him out.

118
00:08:39.686 --> 00:08:41.812
Take me to my throne

119
00:08:41.813 --> 00:08:46.151
and once he returns.
I shall take him prisoner... hm?

120
00:08:46.152 --> 00:08:47.569
And what then?

121
00:08:49.029 --> 00:08:51.489
When Rhaenyra descends
on you with her seven dragons.

122
00:08:51.490 --> 00:08:53.825
and you. without Vhagar.
what then?

123
00:08:55.535 --> 00:08:56.536
W...

124
00:08:57.662 --> 00:08:58.705
Uh...

125
00:09:05.378 --> 00:09:07.004
I have.
over the years.

126
00:09:07.005 --> 00:09:09.506
in anticipation of little bumps
in the road.

127
00:09:09.507 --> 00:09:12.135
moved the greater part
of Harrenhal's gold reserves

128
00:09:12.136 --> 00:09:14.220
to the Iron Bank
in Braavos.

129
00:09:14.221 --> 00:09:16.847
We can live... well

130
00:09:16.848 --> 00:09:20.352
and remain until
what is coming has passed.

131
00:09:20.353 --> 00:09:22.354
(weak laughter)

132
00:09:23.021 --> 00:09:25.690
Y... You want
to take me to Essos

133
00:09:25.691 --> 00:09:28.360
to live with
the goatfuckers.

134
00:09:29.569 --> 00:09:31.571
It's best to live.
I think.

135
00:09:31.905 --> 00:09:34.199
- However you do it.
- Is it?

136
00:09:36.076 --> 00:09:38.078
My dragon is dead.

137
00:09:38.703 --> 00:09:40.746
I am burnt...

138
00:09:40.747 --> 00:09:44.417
and disgusting...
and alone.

139
00:09:45.251 --> 00:09:46.711
And I'm a cripple.

140
00:09:50.423 --> 00:09:51.882
You are not alone.

141
00:09:51.883 --> 00:09:54.843
My cock is destroyed.
did they tell you that?

142
00:09:54.844 --> 00:09:58.723
Yeah. It burst into flames
like a sausage on the spit.

143
00:09:58.724 --> 00:10:00.475
Do not despair.
Your Grace.

144
00:10:00.476 --> 00:10:02.227
There are
better days ahead.

145
00:10:02.602 --> 00:10:05.104
Let your brother
and the Pretender

146
00:10:05.105 --> 00:10:08.191
destroy themselves
in blood and bitterness.

147
00:10:08.192 --> 00:10:09.608
When they are spent.

148
00:10:09.609 --> 00:10:11.111
and their armies
in tatters.

149
00:10:11.112 --> 00:10:12.611
we will return.

150
00:10:12.612 --> 00:10:16.031
and the people
will rise up to meet us.

151
00:10:16.032 --> 00:10:19.889
I can't even piss
without it running down my leg.

152
00:10:19.890 --> 00:10:23.748
They will be tired
of endless deprivation and fear.

153
00:10:25.125 --> 00:10:27.752
They will hail
the returning king...

154
00:10:28.420 --> 00:10:31.256
his father's true heir.

155
00:10:32.674 --> 00:10:35.134
Aegon
the Victorious...

156
00:10:35.135 --> 00:10:37.595
risen from the ashes.

157
00:10:38.638 --> 00:10:40.640
Aegon the Peacemaker.

158
00:10:43.685 --> 00:10:45.687
Aegon the Rebuilder.

159
00:10:49.232 --> 00:10:51.860
Aegon. the Realm's Delight.

160
00:10:53.862 --> 00:10:57.115
{\an8}- (tense music playing)
- (wind blowing)

161
00:11:02.037 --> 00:11:04.039
(heavy breathing)

162
00:11:06.499 --> 00:11:08.501
(water flowing)

163
00:11:24.225 --> 00:11:25.226
(gasps)

164
00:11:36.988 --> 00:11:38.990
♪

165
00:11:39.657 --> 00:11:42.659
Ulf: This is more like it.
Hugh. don't you think?

166
00:11:42.660 --> 00:11:44.996
Hugh: We're meant to be
at the training yards learnin' the commands.

167
00:11:44.997 --> 00:11:46.663
Ulf:
Yeah. and I will go.

168
00:11:46.664 --> 00:11:50.043
but surely they'd not deny me
my pleasure after so long.

169
00:11:50.044 --> 00:11:52.712
- I may never eat fish again.
- (music fades out)

170
00:11:53.588 --> 00:11:55.298
What are you
doing here?

171
00:11:55.840 --> 00:11:57.487
Remove your feet
from the table.

172
00:11:57.488 --> 00:11:59.135
- Ulf: I'd rather not.
- Hugh: Ulf.

173
00:11:59.136 --> 00:12:02.054
It's not up
to you... Ulf.

174
00:12:02.055 --> 00:12:04.973
Who's it up
to then... boy?

175
00:12:04.974 --> 00:12:08.977
He is the prince. Ulf.
Prince Jacaerys Velaryon.

176
00:12:08.978 --> 00:12:12.982
Prince Jacaerys Velaryon.
Right here. (chuckles)

177
00:12:12.983 --> 00:12:14.567
Who'd have
thought it?

178
00:12:14.568 --> 00:12:16.360
He lives here.

179
00:12:16.361 --> 00:12:17.946
I'll have
an apology from you.

180
00:12:18.738 --> 00:12:20.885
Ah!
The young prince!

181
00:12:20.886 --> 00:12:23.034
And look
at that hair.

182
00:12:24.869 --> 00:12:27.538
As dark as they say.

183
00:12:27.539 --> 00:12:30.000
Let them tell us
we don't have Targaryen blood. eh?

184
00:12:30.709 --> 00:12:34.504
- My mother is the queen and...
- Dragonriders both.

185
00:12:34.505 --> 00:12:37.840
You and I...
cut from the same cloth.

186
00:12:37.841 --> 00:12:40.885
It is a sacred inheritance of
which you know nothing.

187
00:12:41.636 --> 00:12:43.512
Forgive him.
my prince.

188
00:12:43.513 --> 00:12:46.391
He is not much
used to the manners of court.

189
00:12:46.392 --> 00:12:48.225
Or any manners
at all. I'd say.

190
00:12:48.226 --> 00:12:51.396
Do you know what has happened
this last hour. hm?

191
00:12:52.564 --> 00:12:54.189
The so-called
prince regent

192
00:12:54.190 --> 00:12:56.067
has burned Sharp Point
down to its stones.

193
00:12:56.068 --> 00:12:58.194
Thousands of its folk
dead or lost.

194
00:12:58.195 --> 00:12:59.863
Its harbor in ashes.

195
00:13:01.072 --> 00:13:03.658
Will you prepare
to face such an enemy?

196
00:13:05.243 --> 00:13:08.079
Or will you stay here
and make yourself easy?

197
00:13:08.080 --> 00:13:10.415
If you hinder
our efforts

198
00:13:10.416 --> 00:13:12.751
through sloth
or unreadiness.

199
00:13:12.752 --> 00:13:14.084
I will see
you hanged.

200
00:13:14.085 --> 00:13:17.380
and your body fed to the dogs
in the street.

201
00:13:17.381 --> 00:13:20.425
I-I meant no disrespect.
my prince.

202
00:13:35.273 --> 00:13:36.899
(indistinct chatter)

203
00:13:36.900 --> 00:13:39.277
Rhaenyra Targaryen:
The new riders are a boon to us.

204
00:13:39.278 --> 00:13:42.030
but now
the deed is done.

205
00:13:42.031 --> 00:13:44.782
I cannot erase
my doubts.

206
00:13:44.783 --> 00:13:46.450
We know little
of who they are.

207
00:13:46.451 --> 00:13:48.953
and what is the strength
of their character.

208
00:13:48.954 --> 00:13:51.456
Addam of Hull. at least.
is known to you.

209
00:13:52.874 --> 00:13:55.125
He's a shipwright
in my employ.

210
00:13:55.126 --> 00:13:58.797
and it is reported to me tha
he is a man of integrity.

211
00:13:58.798 --> 00:14:03.802
I've had little to do with him...
to my regret.

212
00:14:03.803 --> 00:14:06.242
But the beasts
have been claimed.

213
00:14:06.243 --> 00:14:08.682
You now have
a great advantage.

214
00:14:08.683 --> 00:14:10.849
You must strike.
quickly.

215
00:14:10.850 --> 00:14:13.019
while the prince regent
mulls his next action.

216
00:14:14.646 --> 00:14:17.691
I had hoped my advantage
may be in deterrence.

217
00:14:18.858 --> 00:14:20.652
Vhagar has ever been
our foremost threat.

218
00:14:20.653 --> 00:14:22.487
and she is now
overmatched.

219
00:14:22.488 --> 00:14:24.321
Vhagar is not
his only dragon.

220
00:14:24.322 --> 00:14:26.157
W... The third brother
is untested.

221
00:14:26.158 --> 00:14:27.616
has never
left Oldtown.

222
00:14:27.617 --> 00:14:29.661
and his dragon is
younger than Vermax.

223
00:14:29.662 --> 00:14:31.433
But a dragon
nonetheless.

224
00:14:31.434 --> 00:14:33.206
And you forget another.

225
00:14:34.916 --> 00:14:36.167
Helaena?

226
00:14:36.668 --> 00:14:39.045
She does not ride.
She has no taste for it.

227
00:14:39.046 --> 00:14:41.338
She may yet
be compelled.

228
00:14:41.339 --> 00:14:43.424
- And her dragon...
- Dreamfyre.

229
00:14:43.425 --> 00:14:45.510
hatched when
the Conqueror was king.

230
00:14:46.594 --> 00:14:48.512
She is formidable.

231
00:14:48.513 --> 00:14:50.765
Still. Helaena
is no warrior.

232
00:14:53.935 --> 00:14:56.103
Aemond thought
himself invincible.

233
00:14:56.104 --> 00:14:58.273
He has now discovered
he is not.

234
00:14:59.024 --> 00:15:01.276
He'll be angry. desperate.

235
00:15:01.860 --> 00:15:04.070
He will not stop
at burning Sharp Point.

236
00:15:04.071 --> 00:15:06.364
and he will
not be denied.

237
00:15:07.073 --> 00:15:08.408
You speak truly...

238
00:15:09.617 --> 00:15:11.327
though I wish it
was not so.

239
00:15:11.328 --> 00:15:12.954
(soft chuckle)

240
00:15:13.705 --> 00:15:15.707
(indistinct chatter)

241
00:15:16.249 --> 00:15:17.625
How goes
the <i>Sea Snake?</i>

242
00:15:19.252 --> 00:15:20.879
Better than new.

243
00:15:21.755 --> 00:15:23.798
We'll rejoin
the blockade on the morrow.

244
00:15:24.215 --> 00:15:27.552
Let our foes beware.
be they Lannister or Greyjoy.

245
00:15:29.054 --> 00:15:32.724
But... my ship is no longer
the <i>Sea Snake.</i>

246
00:15:33.141 --> 00:15:35.727
She was a testament
to my own glory.

247
00:15:36.644 --> 00:15:38.646
I've given her
a new name.

248
00:15:40.982 --> 00:15:43.234
<i>The Queen Who Never Was.</i>

249
00:15:45.737 --> 00:15:46.905
Rhaenyra:
Corlys...

250
00:15:48.073 --> 00:15:49.741
I thank you.

251
00:15:52.327 --> 00:15:53.952
(soft chuckle)

252
00:15:53.953 --> 00:15:57.582
What I do now...
I do for her.

253
00:16:00.251 --> 00:16:02.294
Your Grace.
you are ready.

254
00:16:02.295 --> 00:16:05.799
You have six dragons
under your banner.

255
00:16:05.800 --> 00:16:08.218
My ships sail
at your command.

256
00:16:08.219 --> 00:16:09.719
and my men serve you.

257
00:16:10.428 --> 00:16:12.200
But the Lannisters
are marching.

258
00:16:12.201 --> 00:16:13.973
and the Hightowers
from Oldtown.

259
00:16:15.100 --> 00:16:18.436
You must crush this beast
at its head

260
00:16:18.437 --> 00:16:21.773
and before too many
days have flown.

261
00:16:25.110 --> 00:16:27.152
There is.
of course...

262
00:16:27.153 --> 00:16:30.615
another player that has yet
to be revealed.

263
00:16:32.617 --> 00:16:34.660
Ah. Your Grace.
a word.

264
00:16:34.661 --> 00:16:38.123
It seems the sheep
on our land has been sold upriver.

265
00:16:38.124 --> 00:16:40.959
My vassals have sent
a drove of swine instead.

266
00:16:40.960 --> 00:16:42.751
Dragons do eat pigs.
I assume?

267
00:16:42.752 --> 00:16:44.691
Caraxes prefers them.
How goes your muster?

268
00:16:44.692 --> 00:16:46.808
We'll be ready to march
in two days' time.

269
00:16:46.809 --> 00:16:48.924
- See to those pigs.
- At once. Your Grace.

270
00:16:48.925 --> 00:16:52.679
Your Grace... Ser Alfred Broome
has come to see you.

271
00:16:52.680 --> 00:16:55.264
(laughs) Interesting.

272
00:16:55.265 --> 00:16:57.266
I am sent as an emissary
from the queen.

273
00:16:57.267 --> 00:16:59.686
to ascertain your movements
and your intentions.

274
00:16:59.687 --> 00:17:01.646
You've arrived
just in time

275
00:17:01.647 --> 00:17:03.481
to see my new
army. Broome.

276
00:17:03.482 --> 00:17:05.316
What do you
think of it?

277
00:17:05.317 --> 00:17:07.109
It's very large.

278
00:17:07.110 --> 00:17:09.236
(Daemon chuckles softly)

279
00:17:09.237 --> 00:17:11.364
Lannister hesitates.

280
00:17:11.823 --> 00:17:14.534
I aim to march on King's Landing
before he can catch me.

281
00:17:14.535 --> 00:17:17.203
May I have a word in private.
Your Grace?

282
00:17:21.875 --> 00:17:23.959
I would speak
honestly with you.

283
00:17:23.960 --> 00:17:25.502
Daemon Targaryen:
I'd expect nothing less.

284
00:17:25.503 --> 00:17:28.340
Alfred Broome: I was faithful to the king.
your brother.

285
00:17:28.341 --> 00:17:30.967
I pledged my banners
to Rhaenyra. his heir.

286
00:17:30.968 --> 00:17:32.844
I will never serve
the usurpers

287
00:17:32.845 --> 00:17:34.720
or the whelps
of Oldtown.

288
00:17:34.721 --> 00:17:36.805
but there are battles
to be fought...

289
00:17:36.806 --> 00:17:39.434
- voice (whispers): Traitor.
- ...and in times like this...

290
00:17:42.520 --> 00:17:44.189
Did you hear
something?

291
00:17:46.107 --> 00:17:48.735
This place will have you barking
at the moon.

292
00:17:51.738 --> 00:17:53.531
While you have
mustered an army.

293
00:17:53.532 --> 00:17:55.240
Rhaenyra
has faltered...

294
00:17:55.241 --> 00:17:57.076
turning aside
from our judgment.

295
00:17:57.077 --> 00:17:59.495
and taking a course.
I myself. deem reckless.

296
00:17:59.496 --> 00:18:03.500
Rhaenyra will chart her own course.
for good or ill.

297
00:18:03.501 --> 00:18:05.460
But you are
a leader of men.

298
00:18:06.795 --> 00:18:09.005
If you declare
yourself.

299
00:18:09.006 --> 00:18:11.216
your lords
will follow you.

300
00:18:11.716 --> 00:18:14.552
I never took you
for a turncloak...

301
00:18:15.553 --> 00:18:17.138
Ser Alfred.

302
00:18:20.058 --> 00:18:22.227
Rhaenyra's
intentions are good.

303
00:18:24.062 --> 00:18:27.649
But what we need.
in this moment...

304
00:18:29.317 --> 00:18:30.735
is a king.

305
00:18:33.405 --> 00:18:36.866
(tense music playing)

306
00:18:36.867 --> 00:18:38.493
(chuckles)

307
00:18:49.254 --> 00:18:50.880
(sighs)

308
00:18:50.881 --> 00:18:52.507
♪

309
00:18:57.595 --> 00:18:59.305
Jasper "Ironrod" Wylde:
<i>It appears that the Pretender</i>

310
00:18:59.306 --> 00:19:01.536
sent boats to collect
those among the smallfolk

311
00:19:01.537 --> 00:19:03.768
who believed they had any drop
of Targaryen blood.

312
00:19:03.769 --> 00:19:05.894
Deception
and subterfuge.

313
00:19:05.895 --> 00:19:09.064
Cowards. all of them.
Put an end to this madness.

314
00:19:09.065 --> 00:19:12.318
Let no vessel come or go from our harbor
without our inspection.

315
00:19:12.319 --> 00:19:14.654
This will hinder the work
of the fishing boats.

316
00:19:14.655 --> 00:19:16.781
The people depend on them
for sustenance.

317
00:19:16.782 --> 00:19:18.449
They will need
no sustenance

318
00:19:18.450 --> 00:19:20.827
if they are slaughtered
by the enemy.

319
00:19:20.828 --> 00:19:23.121
We must all make
our sacrifices.

320
00:19:25.665 --> 00:19:28.001
Helaena Targaryen:
<i>Why does everybody hate us?</i>

321
00:19:28.002 --> 00:19:30.002
Alicent Hightower:
They're unhappy...

322
00:19:30.003 --> 00:19:32.464
and unhappy people look
for someone to hate.

323
00:19:36.134 --> 00:19:38.135
We didn't order
the blockade.

324
00:19:38.136 --> 00:19:41.222
No. but we are the crown.
so they expect us to break it.

325
00:19:42.557 --> 00:19:43.808
Drink this.

326
00:19:50.982 --> 00:19:53.651
I was happier
before I was queen.

327
00:20:00.200 --> 00:20:02.660
What would you think
about leaving this place?

328
00:20:05.372 --> 00:20:07.374
(birds cawing)

329
00:20:11.503 --> 00:20:13.504
Where would I go?

330
00:20:13.505 --> 00:20:15.507
(knocks on door)

331
00:20:19.761 --> 00:20:21.887
The prince regent.
Your Grace.

332
00:20:21.888 --> 00:20:24.015
Helaena. Here you are.
Mother.

333
00:20:26.768 --> 00:20:30.188
- I was just. just going to bed.
- The crown has need of your service.

334
00:20:30.189 --> 00:20:32.732
- Now?
- The Pretender has raised new riders against us.

335
00:20:32.733 --> 00:20:35.402
and we must
answer in kind.

336
00:20:36.611 --> 00:20:38.488
I need you to fly
with Dreamfyre to battle.

337
00:20:38.489 --> 00:20:40.573
- Aemond.
- I do not wish to fight.

338
00:20:40.574 --> 00:20:42.658
Our wishes must take
second place now

339
00:20:42.659 --> 00:20:45.286
to what is necessary
to preserve the throne.

340
00:20:46.204 --> 00:20:48.206
I won't burn anyone.

341
00:20:50.250 --> 00:20:51.709
It isn't a question.

342
00:20:51.710 --> 00:20:53.440
- Aemond.
- They have defiled our birthright.

343
00:20:53.441 --> 00:20:55.170
- made commoners into dragonlords!
- Ow. ow!

344
00:20:55.171 --> 00:20:56.839
- Aemond! Aemond!
- It is a sin and must be punished!

345
00:20:56.840 --> 00:20:58.508
- May I remind you your sister is still the queen?
- Ow!

346
00:20:58.509 --> 00:21:00.384
As you were once!
And you see now

347
00:21:00.385 --> 00:21:02.303
what is the consequence
of your weakness!

348
00:21:02.304 --> 00:21:04.221
We are in peril today
more than yesterday!

349
00:21:04.222 --> 00:21:06.850
Was it peril that moved you to burn
the town of Sharp Point?

350
00:21:06.851 --> 00:21:09.519
Peril or basest fury
at your own humiliation?

351
00:21:09.520 --> 00:21:11.228
Ow!

352
00:21:11.229 --> 00:21:12.730
You wish to rule
the Seven Kingdoms.

353
00:21:12.731 --> 00:21:15.108
but you rain ruin and death
upon its smallfolk

354
00:21:15.109 --> 00:21:17.276
when you've
been insulted

355
00:21:17.277 --> 00:21:19.236
because it makes
you feel strong

356
00:21:19.237 --> 00:21:21.113
and now you seek
to corrupt your sister.

357
00:21:21.114 --> 00:21:23.011
of all our line.
the gentlest and most deserving

358
00:21:23.012 --> 00:21:24.909
- of your protection.
- And who will protect her

359
00:21:24.910 --> 00:21:26.201
if she cannot
protect herself?

360
00:21:26.202 --> 00:21:27.974
And who will she be
if her mind is broken?!

361
00:21:27.975 --> 00:21:29.748
'Tis no longer our rule
that is threatened.

362
00:21:29.749 --> 00:21:31.040
our very lives.

363
00:21:31.041 --> 00:21:32.921
- Would you not have us prevail?
- Not like this.

364
00:21:36.588 --> 00:21:38.423
Not like this!

365
00:21:40.091 --> 00:21:43.261
(light. tense music playing)

366
00:21:55.315 --> 00:21:56.775
Grand Maester Orwyle:
Your Grace.

367
00:21:57.525 --> 00:21:58.777
Grand Maester.

368
00:22:00.153 --> 00:22:02.364
I must again request
your assistance.

369
00:22:03.114 --> 00:22:04.783
I need passage.

370
00:22:05.658 --> 00:22:07.535
And your discretion.

371
00:22:10.288 --> 00:22:13.791
(solemn music playing)

372
00:22:13.792 --> 00:22:16.795
- (quiet chatter)
- (ambient nature sounds)

373
00:22:19.464 --> 00:22:22.300
Gwayne Hightower: Do you think
nothing of your oath...

374
00:22:24.302 --> 00:22:25.720
Lord Commander?

375
00:22:27.889 --> 00:22:30.016
I think of nothing
else. my lord.

376
00:22:31.351 --> 00:22:33.686
Steward's son
from Dorne

377
00:22:33.687 --> 00:22:36.356
fucking the queen
of the Seven Kingdoms.

378
00:22:38.400 --> 00:22:40.984
Former queen.

379
00:22:40.985 --> 00:22:43.404
She has broken no oath.
for all I may have done.

380
00:22:43.405 --> 00:22:46.157
- I could send you to the Wall.
- You could.

381
00:22:46.158 --> 00:22:48.910
Stain the Hightower name
for a generation.

382
00:22:49.327 --> 00:22:52.163
- King's mother and his Hand.
- She is my sister.

383
00:22:53.832 --> 00:22:55.040
(inhales)

384
00:22:55.041 --> 00:22:57.002
She saved my life.

385
00:22:57.919 --> 00:22:59.378
Twice.

386
00:22:59.379 --> 00:23:02.173
Once from the headsman's axe
and once from myself.

387
00:23:05.844 --> 00:23:08.430
Since then. she has been
the beacon I follow.

388
00:23:18.064 --> 00:23:20.692
Do not think I have
no shame in me. ser.

389
00:23:22.068 --> 00:23:24.863
Desire for women
has brought me grief after grief.

390
00:23:25.405 --> 00:23:29.367
- Gwayne: Then resist it.
- (Criston chuckles softly)

391
00:23:29.368 --> 00:23:31.201
Oh. would that
it were so simple.

392
00:23:31.202 --> 00:23:33.913
Your brothers
in the Kingsguard find a way.

393
00:23:37.083 --> 00:23:38.543
Do they?

394
00:23:40.253 --> 00:23:41.921
Mm. perhaps
they do.

395
00:23:43.882 --> 00:23:46.301
Or perhaps all men
are corrupt...

396
00:23:48.053 --> 00:23:50.472
and true honor is a mist

397
00:23:51.389 --> 00:23:52.891
that melts in the morning.

398
00:23:55.477 --> 00:23:58.063
That is a bleak philosophy.

399
00:23:58.064 --> 00:23:59.939
I have no philosophy.

400
00:24:01.274 --> 00:24:03.485
Or rather.
my philosophy was this.

401
00:24:05.904 --> 00:24:07.237
To protect
the righteous

402
00:24:07.238 --> 00:24:09.657
and dispense justice
on the rest.

403
00:24:11.785 --> 00:24:12.994
But now...

404
00:24:16.331 --> 00:24:18.166
You saw what I saw.

405
00:24:23.463 --> 00:24:27.467
The dragons dance.
and men are like dust under their feet.

406
00:24:31.096 --> 00:24:34.599
And all our fine thoughts.
all our... endeavors

407
00:24:34.600 --> 00:24:36.267
are as nothing.

408
00:24:42.148 --> 00:24:44.984
We march now toward
our annihilation.

409
00:24:51.449 --> 00:24:53.993
To die will be
a kind of relief.

410
00:24:58.623 --> 00:25:00.041
Don't you think?

411
00:25:07.382 --> 00:25:10.385
(unsettling music playing)

412
00:25:34.242 --> 00:25:35.994
- (Sharako yells)
- (crowd cheering)

413
00:25:35.995 --> 00:25:38.203
(heavy breathing. grunts)

414
00:25:38.204 --> 00:25:40.540
- (crowd shouting)
- (Sharako laughing)

415
00:25:44.502 --> 00:25:46.713
(crowd shouting. laughing)

416
00:25:47.088 --> 00:25:49.424
(Tyland yells. pants)

417
00:25:51.217 --> 00:25:53.261
(Tyland grunting)

418
00:25:55.180 --> 00:25:56.431
(Sharako laughs)

419
00:25:58.266 --> 00:26:00.268
(yells. grunts)

420
00:26:02.020 --> 00:26:04.022
(heavy breathing)

421
00:26:07.442 --> 00:26:09.069
(groaning)

422
00:26:13.782 --> 00:26:15.033
(laughs)

423
00:26:15.408 --> 00:26:17.827
(crowd chanting "Lohar")

424
00:26:17.828 --> 00:26:19.204
(grunting)

425
00:26:21.081 --> 00:26:22.373
(crowd quiets)

426
00:26:22.374 --> 00:26:23.958
- (grunts)
- (Sharako yelps)

427
00:26:26.211 --> 00:26:28.213
(heavy breathing)

428
00:26:29.047 --> 00:26:31.049
(all silent)

429
00:26:33.051 --> 00:26:34.051
(spits)

430
00:26:39.641 --> 00:26:42.893
You have impressed me.
Lord Tyman.

431
00:26:42.894 --> 00:26:46.398
King's Landing has sent
a most doughty ambassador.

432
00:26:46.399 --> 00:26:48.066
(panting)

433
00:26:49.484 --> 00:26:55.240
I hope... you will testify to the worth
of the ambassador...

434
00:26:55.241 --> 00:26:59.035
by agreeing to his most
(pants) humble request.

435
00:26:59.036 --> 00:27:02.080
I will
most certainly consider it.

436
00:27:02.831 --> 00:27:03.831
(spits)

437
00:27:09.462 --> 00:27:11.256
After dinner.

438
00:27:15.635 --> 00:27:18.263
Have you ever eaten
the flesh of your enemies?

439
00:27:18.264 --> 00:27:19.931
(panting)
What?

440
00:27:22.267 --> 00:27:25.270
I have not
and I would not.

441
00:27:26.938 --> 00:27:31.359
So you reject
the hospitality of my house.

442
00:27:39.325 --> 00:27:42.162
- (laughs)
- (crowd laughs)

443
00:27:42.163 --> 00:27:43.621
A jest. my lord.

444
00:27:44.956 --> 00:27:47.792
(laughing)
What do you take me for?

445
00:27:50.795 --> 00:27:52.005
A jest!

446
00:27:53.048 --> 00:27:54.299
Come.

447
00:27:57.635 --> 00:28:00.472
- (grunts)
- (crowd yells. laughs)

448
00:28:05.185 --> 00:28:07.395
(nearby dragon grumbles)

449
00:28:09.147 --> 00:28:11.566
It does not befit
a prince to pout.

450
00:28:13.360 --> 00:28:14.985
I'm not pouting.

451
00:28:14.986 --> 00:28:16.404
What would you
call it. then?

452
00:28:18.907 --> 00:28:22.160
- I'm reading.
- While your mother waits?

453
00:28:25.997 --> 00:28:27.665
You're angry.

454
00:28:30.835 --> 00:28:32.044
Aren't you?

455
00:28:32.045 --> 00:28:33.546
I don't see what
good it would do.

456
00:28:34.839 --> 00:28:37.028
They are an insult to us.

457
00:28:37.029 --> 00:28:39.218
To what makes us
Targaryens.

458
00:28:39.219 --> 00:28:41.178
If any common lout
can ride a dragon.

459
00:28:41.179 --> 00:28:44.015
- then...
- That does not make me common. Or you.

460
00:28:45.433 --> 00:28:48.061
- You know what I am.
- I don't care.

461
00:28:48.062 --> 00:28:50.187
You are
the crown prince.

462
00:28:50.188 --> 00:28:51.981
the son of
the rightful queen.

463
00:28:51.982 --> 00:28:53.524
and here you are sulking

464
00:28:53.525 --> 00:28:55.026
because you believe that
if not for the dragon

465
00:28:55.027 --> 00:28:56.695
or the trappings
of your station.

466
00:28:56.696 --> 00:28:58.529
that you are nothing.

467
00:28:58.530 --> 00:29:01.157
(chuckles) Do you believe
that you are the first noble heir

468
00:29:01.158 --> 00:29:03.493
who was not sired
by his noble father?

469
00:29:04.119 --> 00:29:06.537
Such is the way
of the world. Jace.

470
00:29:06.538 --> 00:29:09.666
and in resenting it.
you only diminish yourself.

471
00:29:09.667 --> 00:29:11.292
Easy enough
to say.

472
00:29:11.793 --> 00:29:14.337
I've heard the whispers
the whole of my life.

473
00:29:14.338 --> 00:29:16.589
Then prove to them
that you are worthy.

474
00:29:16.590 --> 00:29:18.216
Get up
and take your place

475
00:29:18.217 --> 00:29:19.592
by your mother's side.

476
00:29:21.803 --> 00:29:25.056
(light. tense music playing)

477
00:29:30.395 --> 00:29:32.397
(wind blowing)

478
00:29:34.399 --> 00:29:35.984
(shivering)

479
00:29:37.902 --> 00:29:39.904
♪

480
00:29:44.284 --> 00:29:47.287
Tyland (singing halfheartedly):
♪ Here come my lads. my comely boys ♪

481
00:29:47.288 --> 00:29:49.872
♪ And split your sacks ashore ♪

482
00:29:49.873 --> 00:29:53.084
♪ For you'll be
sail-sailing many days ♪

483
00:29:53.085 --> 00:29:54.711
♪ Afore you get
some more ♪

484
00:29:55.420 --> 00:29:58.089
♪ So grease the mast
and send it up ♪

485
00:29:59.424 --> 00:30:01.593
♪ Betwixt the wind
and water ♪

486
00:30:02.302 --> 00:30:04.554
♪ Hoist. me lads.
and hoist again ♪

487
00:30:05.263 --> 00:30:08.433
♪ Salute the captain's
daughter ♪

488
00:30:12.771 --> 00:30:14.773
Well done.
Lord Tyrod!

489
00:30:23.490 --> 00:30:26.326
Good song.
well delivered.

490
00:30:26.993 --> 00:30:29.307
(indistinct chatter)

491
00:30:29.308 --> 00:30:31.623
(futilely)
It's Tyland.

492
00:30:33.208 --> 00:30:36.251
You have proven yourself
most accommodating.

493
00:30:36.252 --> 00:30:39.464
And more accomplished
than one would think. to look at you.

494
00:30:39.465 --> 00:30:42.509
Hm. Well... Hm.

495
00:30:44.844 --> 00:30:48.056
I will be pleased
to sail at your side.

496
00:30:49.974 --> 00:30:52.394
- Oh.
- And my captains with me.

497
00:30:58.149 --> 00:31:00.150
(chattering stops)

498
00:31:00.151 --> 00:31:03.029
To the Gullet
on the morrow!

499
00:31:03.030 --> 00:31:05.073
(all cheering)

500
00:31:09.494 --> 00:31:11.662
And let the Sea Snake

501
00:31:11.663 --> 00:31:14.165
rue the day
we meet again.

502
00:31:14.166 --> 00:31:16.501
(all cheering)

503
00:31:18.545 --> 00:31:20.880
Ya! My king will
be well pleased.

504
00:31:20.881 --> 00:31:22.527
To friendship!

505
00:31:22.528 --> 00:31:24.175
(cheering)

506
00:31:25.844 --> 00:31:28.847
(percussive music playing)

507
00:31:28.848 --> 00:31:30.724
(indistinct chatter)

508
00:31:36.938 --> 00:31:38.356
It is late.

509
00:31:39.065 --> 00:31:40.900
(Tyland clears throat)

510
00:31:41.568 --> 00:31:43.068
Oh!

511
00:31:43.069 --> 00:31:44.738
Before you go...

512
00:31:45.447 --> 00:31:46.698
Lord Tyland.

513
00:31:46.699 --> 00:31:47.699
Mm.

514
00:31:49.242 --> 00:31:50.868
You are
a handsome man.

515
00:31:50.869 --> 00:31:56.541
and you have proven
your worth and virility.

516
00:31:58.710 --> 00:32:00.712
I wish to have
children by you.

517
00:32:05.133 --> 00:32:08.762
(stammers) You. you...
You want me to...

518
00:32:08.763 --> 00:32:10.055
Indeed.

519
00:32:12.724 --> 00:32:14.768
I want you
to fuck my wives.

520
00:32:19.439 --> 00:32:22.650
How many wives
do you have?

521
00:32:26.404 --> 00:32:28.990
Ulf: (gulps)
More wine here!

522
00:32:30.742 --> 00:32:32.744
Taming a dragon
is thirsty work.

523
00:32:37.749 --> 00:32:40.418
Oh. and some more
of these little birds.

524
00:32:41.419 --> 00:32:42.837
(sighs)

525
00:32:47.342 --> 00:32:48.760
Rhaenyra:
A toast.

526
00:32:50.512 --> 00:32:52.764
To our new riders.

527
00:32:53.932 --> 00:32:56.266
The three of you
are not of noble birth.

528
00:32:56.267 --> 00:32:59.312
but you have done a thing
never dreamed of before now.

529
00:32:59.313 --> 00:33:01.981
- (Ulf chuckling)
- (Jacaerys sighs)

530
00:33:11.116 --> 00:33:14.639
I have entrusted you
with a power only few have known.

531
00:33:14.640 --> 00:33:18.164
And I charge you to take it up
with fealty and respect.

532
00:33:18.998 --> 00:33:22.002
Serve me well. and I will make you
knights of the realm.

533
00:33:23.044 --> 00:33:25.755
Huh? What do you think
of that. boys?

534
00:33:26.297 --> 00:33:28.653
We'll be knights...
just like that.

535
00:33:28.654 --> 00:33:31.011
We will not fail you.
my queen.

536
00:33:32.846 --> 00:33:34.472
What must we do?

537
00:33:37.058 --> 00:33:40.061
I had thought the mere
fact of you might stay the enemy's hand.

538
00:33:41.980 --> 00:33:43.773
But Lord Corlys
is right.

539
00:33:44.149 --> 00:33:47.360
We must strike while
we have the advantage...

540
00:33:48.028 --> 00:33:49.279
and end this war.

541
00:33:49.654 --> 00:33:52.323
Learn your beasts
and your commands.

542
00:33:52.824 --> 00:33:54.451
You will fly
in two days' time.

543
00:33:55.326 --> 00:33:58.955
The strongholds of the usurper.
Oldtown and Lannisport.

544
00:33:58.956 --> 00:34:02.625
and their armies.
all must be subdued.

545
00:34:03.376 --> 00:34:06.212
Alone. without allies.
he will have no choice but to surrender.

546
00:34:06.213 --> 00:34:08.672
You wish for us
to kill innocents.

547
00:34:08.673 --> 00:34:10.717
- And so many.
- Jacaerys Velaryon: It is hard...

548
00:34:11.760 --> 00:34:13.636
but it cannot
be helped.

549
00:34:13.637 --> 00:34:14.679
(Ulf grunts)

550
00:34:18.516 --> 00:34:20.560
We must break the will
of our enemy...

551
00:34:21.561 --> 00:34:22.978
or more will die
in a struggle

552
00:34:22.979 --> 00:34:24.397
that stretches
on without end.

553
00:34:24.398 --> 00:34:25.899
What about Vhagar?

554
00:34:27.192 --> 00:34:31.780
She is fearsome...
but she is one dragon.

555
00:34:33.198 --> 00:34:36.096
The prince regent cannot
defend against all of us.

556
00:34:36.097 --> 00:34:38.995
I'll take him on myself.
Silverwing's a goer. she is.

557
00:34:38.996 --> 00:34:41.206
- We're afraid of nothing.
- Addam of Hull: Hm.

558
00:34:41.706 --> 00:34:44.167
- Even if you are.
- There will be time enough

559
00:34:44.168 --> 00:34:45.794
to see which one
of us is a coward.

560
00:34:47.087 --> 00:34:49.422
I said more of
these little birds!

561
00:34:51.216 --> 00:34:55.387
A knight will comport himself
with grace at the queen's table.

562
00:34:55.804 --> 00:34:57.138
Best make me a knight. then.

563
00:35:01.476 --> 00:35:03.311
You forget yourself...

564
00:35:04.938 --> 00:35:06.147
friend.

565
00:35:08.233 --> 00:35:10.526
(scoffs)

566
00:35:10.527 --> 00:35:12.570
A sense of humor
would do you all good.

567
00:35:17.409 --> 00:35:19.077
(footsteps approach)

568
00:35:23.748 --> 00:35:26.835
(whispers) There is a message from Harrenhal.
Your Grace.

569
00:35:33.299 --> 00:35:34.550
Daemon?

570
00:35:34.551 --> 00:35:37.574
The castellan.
Ser Simon Strong.

571
00:35:37.575 --> 00:35:40.597
Daemon has raised
his army...

572
00:35:40.598 --> 00:35:43.601
- but Ser Simon fears treachery.
- (sighs)

573
00:35:46.938 --> 00:35:48.773
I will not allow it.

574
00:35:50.859 --> 00:35:51.860
Addam...

575
00:35:53.111 --> 00:35:54.279
come with me.

576
00:36:00.118 --> 00:36:01.286
{\an8}Ulf: Thank you.

577
00:36:02.620 --> 00:36:03.621
{\an8}Birds.

578
00:36:08.376 --> 00:36:10.378
(water dripping)

579
00:36:25.310 --> 00:36:27.354
Do you never sleep. witch?

580
00:36:32.317 --> 00:36:34.402
I'm goin'
to the godswood.

581
00:36:44.329 --> 00:36:46.331
(wind blowing)

582
00:37:00.762 --> 00:37:04.808
(antlered human shape
clip-clopping. grumbles)

583
00:37:04.809 --> 00:37:07.852
(eerie music playing)

584
00:37:12.190 --> 00:37:15.193
When you came here.
you were a closed fist.

585
00:37:17.696 --> 00:37:21.366
You wished to bend
the world to your will.

586
00:37:23.952 --> 00:37:26.663
But you've discovered.
I think. that...

587
00:37:26.664 --> 00:37:29.290
this world will
not be governed.

588
00:37:35.797 --> 00:37:39.217
There are omens here
for those who seek them.

589
00:37:42.679 --> 00:37:44.430
You do not scoff?

590
00:37:44.431 --> 00:37:47.892
- I'm no longer inclined to.
- (Alys chuckles)

591
00:37:49.102 --> 00:37:51.104
I'm pleased to hear it.

592
00:37:51.105 --> 00:37:53.148
♪

593
00:38:02.782 --> 00:38:06.286
Do you wish. then.
to learn what is given to you?

594
00:38:14.627 --> 00:38:16.629
All your life.
you have sought to command

595
00:38:16.630 --> 00:38:18.298
your own fate.

596
00:38:20.633 --> 00:38:22.864
(grabs Daemon's hand)

597
00:38:22.865 --> 00:38:25.096
But today you are ready.

598
00:38:25.097 --> 00:38:27.140
♪

599
00:38:42.364 --> 00:38:44.406
♪

600
00:38:44.407 --> 00:38:46.618
(bark crackling)

601
00:38:48.953 --> 00:38:50.955
(music intensifies)

602
00:38:50.956 --> 00:38:52.957
(crackling)

603
00:38:56.961 --> 00:38:58.963
(raven cawing)

604
00:38:58.964 --> 00:39:01.132
♪

605
00:39:02.550 --> 00:39:04.552
(soldiers fighting)

606
00:39:14.646 --> 00:39:16.064
(explosion booms)

607
00:39:16.981 --> 00:39:19.650
(light music playing)

608
00:39:19.651 --> 00:39:22.320
(dragon calls. screeches)

609
00:39:26.866 --> 00:39:28.868
♪

610
00:39:42.674 --> 00:39:45.677
(powerful music playing)

611
00:39:48.596 --> 00:39:51.599
Helaena (echoes):
It's all a story...

612
00:39:59.858 --> 00:40:02.527
and you are but
one part in it.

613
00:40:04.404 --> 00:40:06.655
You know your part.

614
00:40:06.656 --> 00:40:09.659
- (music fades out)
- (wind blowing)

615
00:40:09.660 --> 00:40:11.703
(bark crackling)

616
00:40:16.708 --> 00:40:19.544
<i>You know what you must do.</i>

617
00:40:19.545 --> 00:40:21.212
(footsteps approach)

618
00:40:27.719 --> 00:40:28.928
Sister.

619
00:40:29.721 --> 00:40:31.598
We share
the same blood.

620
00:40:31.599 --> 00:40:32.891
you and I.

621
00:40:33.808 --> 00:40:36.644
I know you wish
no harm to anyone.

622
00:40:38.938 --> 00:40:41.273
But in a time
like this.

623
00:40:41.274 --> 00:40:43.943
when the good
of the realm depends on us...

624
00:40:47.072 --> 00:40:50.367
{\an8}Our mother is not
a dragonrider.

625
00:40:50.368 --> 00:40:52.368
{\an8}She cannot understand

626
00:40:52.369 --> 00:40:55.413
that you and I have
a truer call to heed.

627
00:41:00.126 --> 00:41:01.753
Come with me...

628
00:41:02.962 --> 00:41:04.422
to Harrenhal?

629
00:41:06.424 --> 00:41:09.427
We will lay waste
to Daemon and his army.

630
00:41:10.261 --> 00:41:15.392
Let our enemy see that
we will answer outrage with outrage.

631
00:41:15.393 --> 00:41:17.435
And if I refuse?

632
00:41:20.355 --> 00:41:22.982
Will you burn me
as you did Aegon?

633
00:41:27.028 --> 00:41:29.656
- That is a lie.
- I saw it.

634
00:41:33.368 --> 00:41:37.163
You burned him
and you let him fall.

635
00:41:41.167 --> 00:41:43.169
What you say is treason.

636
00:41:45.630 --> 00:41:48.008
Aegon will be king again.

637
00:41:51.136 --> 00:41:53.513
He's yet to see victory.

638
00:41:54.639 --> 00:41:57.225
He sits on
a wooden throne.

639
00:41:57.976 --> 00:41:59.394
And you...

640
00:42:03.898 --> 00:42:05.900
(whispers)
you'll be dead.

641
00:42:08.653 --> 00:42:11.489
You were swallowed up
in the God's Eye.

642
00:42:11.490 --> 00:42:13.324
and you were
never seen again.

643
00:42:15.493 --> 00:42:18.704
(light. tense music playing)

644
00:42:18.705 --> 00:42:21.791
(whispers)
I could have you killed.

645
00:42:21.792 --> 00:42:24.878
(softly) It wouldn't
change anything.

646
00:42:26.004 --> 00:42:28.006
♪

647
00:42:36.890 --> 00:42:40.518
- (intense music playing)
- (Syrax roars)

648
00:42:40.519 --> 00:42:42.562
(Seasmoke roars)

649
00:42:45.690 --> 00:42:47.692
(Caraxes grumbles)

650
00:42:50.779 --> 00:42:52.197
(roars)

651
00:43:02.082 --> 00:43:04.708
♪

652
00:43:04.709 --> 00:43:06.753
(all yelling)

653
00:43:10.423 --> 00:43:12.884
(singers vocalizing)

654
00:43:15.470 --> 00:43:17.472
(dragons calling)

655
00:43:27.273 --> 00:43:28.900
(screeches)

656
00:43:35.073 --> 00:43:36.491
(roars)

657
00:43:39.828 --> 00:43:41.830
♪

658
00:43:45.500 --> 00:43:48.545
I am the castellan.
Ser Simon Strong. Your Grace.

659
00:43:48.546 --> 00:43:49.754
Well met.

660
00:43:50.755 --> 00:43:52.756
Welcome to Harrenhal.
my queen.

661
00:43:52.757 --> 00:43:55.113
I did not think
to see you here yourself.

662
00:43:55.114 --> 00:43:57.470
(exhales) Your message
gave me much concern.

663
00:43:57.471 --> 00:43:59.973
Yes. I must admit
I had reason to fear.

664
00:44:02.100 --> 00:44:03.768
But come.
see for yourself.

665
00:44:08.106 --> 00:44:10.108
(Seasmoke calls)

666
00:44:14.237 --> 00:44:16.281
(indistinct chatter)

667
00:44:32.630 --> 00:44:34.798
(chatter quiets)

668
00:44:34.799 --> 00:44:36.968
(Syrax screeching)

669
00:44:38.720 --> 00:44:40.138
(roars)

670
00:44:45.477 --> 00:44:47.144
(silence)

671
00:44:47.145 --> 00:44:50.023
(light. tense music playing)

672
00:45:19.678 --> 00:45:21.680
♪

673
00:45:34.025 --> 00:45:36.403
I wasn't
expecting you.

674
00:45:38.905 --> 00:45:41.116
That seems rather
a lapse in foresight.

675
00:45:44.369 --> 00:45:48.081
- I see you have done well here.
- They are sworn to me.

676
00:45:48.082 --> 00:45:50.250
And not a moment
too soon.

677
00:45:55.130 --> 00:45:57.382
And to whom
are you sworn?

678
00:46:13.565 --> 00:46:15.567
{\an8}(speaking High Valyrian)

679
00:46:32.584 --> 00:46:35.253
{\an8}(speaking High Valyrian)

680
00:46:54.981 --> 00:46:57.608
The realm's only hope...

681
00:46:57.609 --> 00:47:00.194
is a leader
who can unite it

682
00:47:00.195 --> 00:47:02.781
and my brother
chose... you.

683
00:47:05.867 --> 00:47:08.870
(light music playing)

684
00:47:21.966 --> 00:47:24.177
You are the true queen.
Rhaenyra.

685
00:47:25.178 --> 00:47:27.471
First of Her Name.

686
00:47:27.472 --> 00:47:29.516
Protector of the Realm.

687
00:47:30.183 --> 00:47:34.145
I am meant to serve you.
and all of these with me.

688
00:47:34.146 --> 00:47:36.105
until death

689
00:47:36.106 --> 00:47:38.525
or the end of our story.

690
00:47:42.987 --> 00:47:45.990
(music intensifies)

691
00:48:04.342 --> 00:48:06.386
(music softens)

692
00:48:11.016 --> 00:48:13.018
{\an8}(speaking High Valyrian)

693
00:48:21.026 --> 00:48:23.028
{\an8}(speaking High Valyrian)

694
00:48:28.199 --> 00:48:29.784
My queen.

695
00:48:39.794 --> 00:48:43.173
(shouting) For every one of us
who falls...

696
00:48:43.174 --> 00:48:45.424
a hundred of them!

697
00:48:45.425 --> 00:48:48.553
There will be
no mercy!

698
00:48:48.928 --> 00:48:51.514
We fight for our queen!

699
00:48:51.515 --> 00:48:53.223
(all cheering)

700
00:48:53.224 --> 00:48:56.227
(heroic music playing)

701
00:49:00.398 --> 00:49:02.400
(Daemon shouting)

702
00:49:04.402 --> 00:49:06.404
♪

703
00:49:16.748 --> 00:49:19.084
(music softens)

704
00:49:19.085 --> 00:49:20.752
(cranking)

705
00:49:22.128 --> 00:49:24.130
(indistinct chatter)

706
00:49:31.805 --> 00:49:33.807
(seagulls cawing)

707
00:49:36.601 --> 00:49:38.770
You sent for me.
Lord Hand.

708
00:49:40.605 --> 00:49:42.816
Gulls are flying
low today.

709
00:49:43.608 --> 00:49:46.110
The weather
will change.

710
00:49:46.111 --> 00:49:48.737
Not until late.
I think. but...

711
00:49:48.738 --> 00:49:52.095
- I will ready the storm sails.
- We join the blockade.

712
00:49:52.096 --> 00:49:55.453
and are like to find ourselves in peril.
sooner than late.

713
00:49:56.538 --> 00:50:00.000
I wish to set out on good terms
with my first mate.

714
00:50:00.625 --> 00:50:02.334
Have I been remiss
in my duties?

715
00:50:02.335 --> 00:50:05.005
You've done what
is asked of you. and more.

716
00:50:05.839 --> 00:50:09.175
But you are curt...
silent.

717
00:50:09.176 --> 00:50:12.512
and the men
find you distant.

718
00:50:13.221 --> 00:50:15.807
You cannot lead
if you do not inspire.

719
00:50:16.224 --> 00:50:18.852
Well. I never asked to lead.
as you well know.

720
00:50:21.688 --> 00:50:24.733
You have been given a position to
which all who serve here aspire.

721
00:50:27.318 --> 00:50:29.319
Forgive me. my lord.

722
00:50:29.320 --> 00:50:31.573
I will endeavor
to improve myself.

723
00:50:32.407 --> 00:50:34.409
(birds cawing)

724
00:50:35.702 --> 00:50:38.163
(softly)
I am trying to help you.

725
00:50:44.669 --> 00:50:46.171
You want
to help me?

726
00:50:48.048 --> 00:50:50.342
Is this the help
you offer after all these years?

727
00:50:50.343 --> 00:50:52.594
A reminder
to be grateful?

728
00:50:53.428 --> 00:50:54.846
I mean no offense.

729
00:50:55.680 --> 00:50:56.890
You may go.

730
00:51:00.518 --> 00:51:02.729
Do you know what
it was like for us?

731
00:51:04.022 --> 00:51:06.231
To grow up
fatherless...

732
00:51:06.232 --> 00:51:08.213
to be sneered upon
as bastards.

733
00:51:08.214 --> 00:51:10.194
never sure of the bread
to feed us?

734
00:51:10.195 --> 00:51:12.572
D-D-Do you know
what hunger does to a boy?

735
00:51:13.615 --> 00:51:15.908
What grief does?

736
00:51:15.909 --> 00:51:18.370
- Or shame?
- You are dismissed.

737
00:51:18.787 --> 00:51:21.268
I sold fish
in the market

738
00:51:21.269 --> 00:51:23.749
from cold dawn
until sunset.

739
00:51:23.750 --> 00:51:26.565
putting by coppers
to stave off the winter.

740
00:51:26.566 --> 00:51:29.381
and I watched the man
who sired me walk past

741
00:51:29.382 --> 00:51:32.216
with his son and heir

742
00:51:32.217 --> 00:51:35.220
with a fur
around his shoulders...

743
00:51:35.804 --> 00:51:40.809
choosing sweetmeats
to eat after supper by the fire.

744
00:51:42.936 --> 00:51:45.083
And now that boy is dead.

745
00:51:45.084 --> 00:51:47.231
And his sister before him.

746
00:51:47.232 --> 00:51:48.941
And the heir
that took his place.

747
00:51:48.942 --> 00:51:52.612
And now. now. now
you remember I live.

748
00:51:54.114 --> 00:51:56.198
Now you wish to...

749
00:51:56.199 --> 00:51:58.827
suddenly to scatter
the crumbs of your favor.

750
00:52:01.329 --> 00:52:05.417
I am an honorable man.
and I will serve you because I must.

751
00:52:06.001 --> 00:52:08.919
But if it is
all the same.

752
00:52:08.920 --> 00:52:13.425
I will decline
any offers of help.

753
00:52:15.468 --> 00:52:17.470
If I survive
this war...

754
00:52:17.846 --> 00:52:20.265
I will continue
as I began...

755
00:52:22.100 --> 00:52:23.309
alone.

756
00:52:27.814 --> 00:52:30.817
(solemn music playing)

757
00:52:47.208 --> 00:52:48.835
(panting)

758
00:52:51.671 --> 00:52:54.736
- (dragon calls)
- (gasps)

759
00:52:54.737 --> 00:52:57.802
(tense. exciting music playing)

760
00:53:01.556 --> 00:53:03.641
(dragon calls)

761
00:53:10.857 --> 00:53:13.151
(music fades out)

762
00:53:14.652 --> 00:53:18.156
Mysaria: You have done what
no one else would dream of.

763
00:53:18.157 --> 00:53:20.367
and you have
been rewarded.

764
00:53:21.076 --> 00:53:23.328
The gods
favor you.

765
00:53:24.245 --> 00:53:27.290
They put the means
to victory in your hands.

766
00:53:27.291 --> 00:53:31.502
And yet. to claim it.
I must strike

767
00:53:31.503 --> 00:53:34.964
and in striking.
I doom thousands to their deaths.

768
00:53:34.965 --> 00:53:37.008
(dragons grumbling)

769
00:53:39.844 --> 00:53:42.222
I do not believe
my father would've wished this.

770
00:53:43.098 --> 00:53:45.349
He left you
with no choice.

771
00:53:45.350 --> 00:53:49.019
Be strong.
You know you are just.

772
00:53:49.020 --> 00:53:50.855
You must not let
the Realm fall to those

773
00:53:50.856 --> 00:53:53.900
who care for power
more than peace.

774
00:53:53.901 --> 00:53:56.194
You must prevail.

775
00:53:59.197 --> 00:54:01.199
And who pays the price?

776
00:54:05.704 --> 00:54:08.707
(dragons grumbling. screeching)

777
00:54:14.421 --> 00:54:16.047
(bangs on door)

778
00:54:19.217 --> 00:54:20.426
Come.

779
00:54:20.427 --> 00:54:22.470
(door opens)

780
00:54:24.973 --> 00:54:26.975
Begging your pardon.
Your Grace.

781
00:54:40.405 --> 00:54:42.407
I had to see you.

782
00:54:51.249 --> 00:54:53.292
- Who knows?
- None save my protector.

783
00:54:53.293 --> 00:54:55.337
He laid down his sword
at your gate.

784
00:54:58.131 --> 00:54:59.591
(sighs)

785
00:55:05.096 --> 00:55:09.309
I've been. I think...
mistaken.

786
00:55:11.311 --> 00:55:13.604
In what?

787
00:55:13.605 --> 00:55:16.815
I was raised to believe there was
an order to things.

788
00:55:16.816 --> 00:55:21.112
that there was security
in following the paths laid out for us.

789
00:55:21.988 --> 00:55:23.238
I resented you.
I think.

790
00:55:23.239 --> 00:55:25.450
for... caring so little
for any of it.

791
00:55:25.451 --> 00:55:28.161
for knowing
what you wanted.

792
00:55:28.703 --> 00:55:30.747
I did not know
what I wanted.

793
00:55:31.289 --> 00:55:33.458
I knew only what
was expected of me.

794
00:55:36.711 --> 00:55:39.964
- Why have you come here?
- Because I lost my way.

795
00:55:39.965 --> 00:55:42.634
Or rather.
it was taken from me.

796
00:55:43.051 --> 00:55:45.135
All those I put
my faith in. my...

797
00:55:45.136 --> 00:55:48.098
- m-my husband. my father. my lover. my son...
- Ooh.

798
00:55:48.099 --> 00:55:49.932
The incorruptible queen

799
00:55:49.933 --> 00:55:51.475
sullies herself
with a lover.

800
00:55:51.476 --> 00:55:53.520
Do not judge me
for what you yourself have done.

801
00:55:54.187 --> 00:55:56.898
Your father died.
I took comfort with another.

802
00:55:57.482 --> 00:56:01.152
- I too have desires.
- Yes. but you alone made virtue your banner.

803
00:56:01.153 --> 00:56:04.280
And I clung to it...
in defiance of you.

804
00:56:04.281 --> 00:56:06.908
I think. who
so disdained it.

805
00:56:17.836 --> 00:56:20.045
I have been
alone. of late.

806
00:56:20.046 --> 00:56:22.277
I walked outside
the walls of the city

807
00:56:22.278 --> 00:56:24.509
and I felt a weight
lifted from me.

808
00:56:24.843 --> 00:56:27.470
- How lovely for you.
- I thought. for the first time.

809
00:56:27.471 --> 00:56:29.514
what I would choose...

810
00:56:30.056 --> 00:56:31.974
if not for the duty
I put before all else.

811
00:56:31.975 --> 00:56:35.854
(chuckles) Shall you cast your son
down and rule alone?

812
00:56:35.855 --> 00:56:38.523
No. I do not wish to rule.
I wish to live.

813
00:56:39.065 --> 00:56:41.963
To be free of all
this endless plotting and striving.

814
00:56:41.964 --> 00:56:44.863
The crown will pursue war
and victory at any cost.

815
00:56:44.864 --> 00:56:48.074
I... (sniffles)
But as for me...

816
00:56:49.784 --> 00:56:53.413
I would take my daughter
and her child and leave it all behind.

817
00:56:54.706 --> 00:56:58.376
(chuckles)
It's too late... Alicent.

818
00:56:59.627 --> 00:57:02.422
You said it yourself.
Blood has been shed.

819
00:57:02.423 --> 00:57:04.424
cities burned.
armies march.

820
00:57:04.425 --> 00:57:06.259
and you wish
to wash your hands

821
00:57:06.260 --> 00:57:08.011
of what you yourself
set in motion.

822
00:57:08.012 --> 00:57:09.762
Oh. the arrogance
of blaming me.

823
00:57:09.763 --> 00:57:11.660
as if you would not
have been challenged regardless.

824
00:57:11.661 --> 00:57:13.860
Did not your hand
bring it forth like a midwife?

825
00:57:13.861 --> 00:57:16.061
I did only what
I thought your father wanted.

826
00:57:18.229 --> 00:57:19.898
Oh. go then.

827
00:57:21.107 --> 00:57:22.567
Leave us behind.
as you say.

828
00:57:22.568 --> 00:57:24.110
(scoffs)
Rhaenyra.

829
00:57:24.903 --> 00:57:27.530
- Wander in the wilderness.
- (Alicent sighs)

830
00:57:27.531 --> 00:57:29.574
What has it got
to do with me?

831
00:57:33.912 --> 00:57:36.915
Did you come here
thinking you would be absolved?

832
00:57:42.671 --> 00:57:44.089
(sighs)

833
00:57:55.975 --> 00:57:58.603
He never stopped loving your mother.
you know?

834
00:57:59.312 --> 00:58:01.106
He was very fond of me.
and I of him.

835
00:58:01.107 --> 00:58:03.273
but...

836
00:58:03.274 --> 00:58:05.485
she was the vision
that sustained him

837
00:58:06.444 --> 00:58:07.611
even after
she herself

838
00:58:07.612 --> 00:58:10.072
had slipped from his grasp.
it was

839
00:58:10.073 --> 00:58:11.825
his love for her
that kept him resolute

840
00:58:11.826 --> 00:58:13.659
in his choice
of heir.

841
00:58:13.660 --> 00:58:16.121
And yet. you believe
he wavered at the end.

842
00:58:22.544 --> 00:58:24.546
Why have you come here?

843
00:58:25.171 --> 00:58:26.631
(sniffles)

844
00:58:27.298 --> 00:58:30.301
Aemond will soon fly to join Cole
in the Riverlands.

845
00:58:31.219 --> 00:58:32.678
(deep breath)

846
00:58:32.679 --> 00:58:34.139
When he's gone...

847
00:58:34.681 --> 00:58:36.932
Helaena as queen will be
the crown's authority.

848
00:58:36.933 --> 00:58:39.144
If you come then to King's Landing.
I will see to it

849
00:58:39.145 --> 00:58:40.936
that our guards
throw down their arms.

850
00:58:40.937 --> 00:58:43.982
we will open the gates.
we will shed no blood.

851
00:58:44.816 --> 00:58:47.402
- You will enter as a conqueror.
- (laughs)

852
00:58:48.653 --> 00:58:50.655
Already you have
the stronger hand.

853
00:58:51.823 --> 00:58:53.198
Once you take the throne...

854
00:58:53.199 --> 00:58:56.703
(deep breath)
this senseless war must end.

855
00:58:59.330 --> 00:59:00.749
(softly)
Right.

856
00:59:05.003 --> 00:59:06.171
What of Aegon?

857
00:59:13.553 --> 00:59:16.765
He's broken
beyond recognition.

858
00:59:18.266 --> 00:59:21.269
He lies in the dark.
in pain and terror.

859
00:59:21.770 --> 00:59:23.396
He has many faults.
but...

860
00:59:24.397 --> 00:59:25.647
he still heeds his mother.

861
00:59:25.648 --> 00:59:27.066
I believe I can
prevail upon him

862
00:59:27.067 --> 00:59:30.362
- to bend the knee. if indeed...
- No! Still...

863
00:59:30.363 --> 00:59:32.030
you defend him.

864
00:59:33.740 --> 00:59:37.077
Still you imagine you
can have all you want

865
00:59:37.078 --> 00:59:38.577
without paying
too high a price.

866
00:59:38.578 --> 00:59:40.872
- a price I had no choice but to pay.
- What I want

867
00:59:40.873 --> 00:59:42.874
is to set things right.

868
00:59:44.918 --> 00:59:46.752
If I am to take
the throne.

869
00:59:46.753 --> 00:59:50.090
I must put an end
to the opposition.

870
00:59:50.091 --> 00:59:51.548
I must take
Aegon's head.

871
00:59:51.549 --> 00:59:53.510
And I have to do it
for all to see.

872
00:59:53.511 --> 00:59:55.136
You know this.

873
00:59:56.888 --> 00:59:59.724
However you may try to evade it.
you know this.

874
01:00:10.568 --> 01:00:11.778
Choose.

875
01:00:12.821 --> 01:00:14.823
(deep breath)

876
01:00:21.287 --> 01:00:24.124
Will you shrink from what
you set out to do?

877
01:00:24.125 --> 01:00:26.167
Or will you
see it through...

878
01:00:27.460 --> 01:00:29.129
and make your sacrifice?

879
01:00:34.259 --> 01:00:36.261
A son for a son.

880
01:00:54.863 --> 01:00:56.281
(exhales)

881
01:00:59.367 --> 01:01:00.785
(sniffles)

882
01:01:08.209 --> 01:01:09.461
(sighs)

883
01:01:13.548 --> 01:01:15.550
(deep breath)

884
01:01:16.801 --> 01:01:18.970
(both crying softly)

885
01:01:29.397 --> 01:01:31.441
You are much changed.

886
01:01:31.983 --> 01:01:35.153
(sniffling) Let us be done
with this. please.

887
01:01:37.489 --> 01:01:39.908
And what do I do
with you now?

888
01:01:41.743 --> 01:01:45.372
You let me go.
to do what I promised.

889
01:01:46.664 --> 01:01:48.875
And you fly to the Red Keep
in three days' time.

890
01:01:48.876 --> 01:01:51.106
and you take
your throne.

891
01:01:51.107 --> 01:01:53.338
Or you take me
for a liar.

892
01:01:54.255 --> 01:01:55.632
I have neither
weapon nor armor.

893
01:01:55.633 --> 01:01:56.965
My life itself
is forfeit.

894
01:01:56.966 --> 01:02:00.053
I... cast myself
on the mercy of a friend

895
01:02:00.054 --> 01:02:02.097
who once loved me.

896
01:02:04.015 --> 01:02:05.600
History will paint
you a villain.

897
01:02:09.938 --> 01:02:11.940
A cold queen...

898
01:02:14.526 --> 01:02:17.195
grasping for power.
and then defeated.

899
01:02:17.862 --> 01:02:19.864
Let them think
what they must.

900
01:02:22.367 --> 01:02:24.619
I am at last myself...

901
01:02:25.537 --> 01:02:30.125
with no ambition greater than to walk
where I please and to breathe the open air.

902
01:02:32.711 --> 01:02:35.380
To die unremarked
and unnoticed...

903
01:02:36.965 --> 01:02:38.591
and be free.

904
01:02:42.387 --> 01:02:44.764
You speak as if
from a distant dream.

905
01:02:45.724 --> 01:02:47.142
Come with me.

906
01:02:51.146 --> 01:02:55.150
My part is here.
whether I will or no.

907
01:02:56.276 --> 01:02:58.903
It was decided
for me long ago.

908
01:03:05.410 --> 01:03:07.245
(softly)
Go.

909
01:03:11.958 --> 01:03:14.961
(melancholy music playing)

910
01:03:33.271 --> 01:03:35.106
(music intensifies)

911
01:04:05.345 --> 01:04:06.971
(panting)

912
01:04:07.681 --> 01:04:09.683
♪

913
01:04:14.312 --> 01:04:17.482
(tense. anticipatory
music playing)

914
01:04:31.329 --> 01:04:33.665
(roars)

915
01:04:41.756 --> 01:04:43.758
♪

916
01:05:03.570 --> 01:05:05.572
♪

917
01:05:20.253 --> 01:05:22.255
♪

918
01:05:40.482 --> 01:05:42.484
♪

919
01:06:13.473 --> 01:06:15.475
♪

920
01:06:23.441 --> 01:06:25.110
(panting)

921
01:06:29.781 --> 01:06:31.783
(dragon grumbles)

922
01:06:36.037 --> 01:06:37.288
(roars)

923
01:06:38.123 --> 01:06:40.125
♪

924
01:06:52.512 --> 01:06:54.973
(singers vocalizing)

925
01:07:13.074 --> 01:07:15.076
(animals chattering)

926
01:07:20.331 --> 01:07:22.166
♪

927
01:07:22.167 --> 01:07:24.252
(vocalizing continues)

928
01:07:45.398 --> 01:07:47.859
(music. vocalizing fades out)

929
01:07:51.696 --> 01:07:54.699
(intense music playing)

930
01:08:25.271 --> 01:08:27.273
♪

931
01:08:44.290 --> 01:08:46.751
(singers vocalizing)

932
01:08:58.430 --> 01:09:00.598
(music. vocalizing fades out)

